sentences.english: Hideyoshi himself brought along two portable teahouses in starkly contrasting styles.

sentences.english: When it comes to their political backgrounds and personal style, the two presidential candidates are quite different.

sentences.english: Different regions and circuits of the brain mature at very different rates.

sentences.english: It is nto the same thing to have a bare field in January and in Juluy.

sentences.english: That is to say, we lie to develop level disparately.

sentences.english: But reality on the street was teaching him a very different lesson.

sentences.english: I dont know love yet had beauty and wealth, but grew up to become different.

sentences.english: Those two ideas are quite distinct from each other.
so their grammar is very ingrained in Spanish, which is different than English.

sentences.english: It's very different from the east side of Manhattan which is, quiet, quiet, quiet.

sentences.english: To read prodigiously and to read profitably are two very different things.
sentences.chinese: 读大量的书与读有益的书是截然不同的事情。

sentences.english: It turns out the advice that shoppers receive will differ radically from one wine shop to the next.
